      "description": "We showed in Volume Fourteen that King Saul (Ṭālūt)—the first Monarch of the Children of Israel—probably began his rule sometime around 1020 BCE. He was then succeeded by Israel’s second King, the Prophet David (Dāwūd) (d. ca. 970 BCE),…",
