              "content": "<p> Greater Syria is to the North of Medina. Another transmission states that the wind will come from the Yaman, which, of course, is to the South. Al- Imām al-Nawawī notes that it is probable that there are two winds—one from Greater Syria and the other from the Yaman. He observes that it may be true the “the good wind” originates in the two different places, but later comes together to become a single wind.  </p>",
